(a) The registration of older women (Seven Regions): Some criticism has again been reported (Six Regions) but on a very reduced scale, dying away to nothing the last week.
\par 
\par The chief ground of criticism was that many young people are not yet fully employed. It is also believed by a few that some factories have idle time; aloe that the women's health will be affected. Others complain of the tactless manner of Ministry of L
abour interviewers.
\par 
\par Women in the South-East are reported on the whole to have welcomed the registration and to be impatient with the attitude of some male M.Ps.
\par 
\par (b) Misuse of labour (Five Regions): The view persists that labour is still not being used to the best advantage and reference is again made to:
