\par 
\par There has been some appreciative comment in Northern Ireland and the South Eastern
 District on the reduction in coupon value of wooden-soled shoes (November 22) and cheaper shoes (November 25). In four other Regions, however, opinion is more critical: "Two pairs of rotten ones at ten coupons not worth one good pair'''. It is suggested 
this was done to enable manufacturers to get rid of shoddy goods; also, that wooden-soled shoes are "simply a flop" because they wear out too quickly.
\par 
\par During the last four weeks the following, familiar topics have boon reported (See also Constant Topics, Nos, 2.5.16.22):
