\par (b) The: aren't always fairly distributed (Four Regions). Some children failed to get any of the last allocation and there is a feeling that oranges sometimes go to favour
ed customers instead. One report mentions people with time to queue getting oranges from two or three different shops. It is suggested that they should be distributed through schools and c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7681550 
linics that shops should be compelled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6970953  to display notices when an allocation is available.
