\par The inadequacy of the cooking ration (Six Regions), particularly at Christmas time. 
\par 
\par Canadian apples have boon looked forward to with pleasure (Five Regions); and there is some impatience at their non-appearance, particularly in the Northern Region where it is asked: "Why should they so to the south}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10909220  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6970953 they have plenty of English apples and can grow their own?" Supplies were greatly appreciated in Scotland, but "control of sole would have been welcomed, as supplies often went t
o shop-crawlers before workers could get them".
\par 
\par The difficulty of getting invalid foods (Three Regions): Ovaltine is particularly mentioned and so is whiskey which, oven when ordered by the doctor, is often unobtainable for other than regular customers. Th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7681550 
e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6970953  "nastiness" of wartime cakes (Three Regions).
